fields.Title: WHIRLING / CEILING FAN
fields.Description: The ceiling fan is spinning like the blades of some rickety old airship about to fall on you. A truly horrendous neck-tie has somehow attached itself to one of the blades.

fields.Title: You: "Grab your chest."
fields.Dialogue Text: Grab your chest.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "Still ongoing. Now is a good time t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Still ongoing. Now is a good time to start worrying.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "You can take it. Just breathe."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can take it. Just breathe.

fields.Title: You: "Grab your chest."
fields.Dialogue Text: Grab your chest.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "The lights are off."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lights are off.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Still ongoing. Now is a good time t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Still ongoing. Now is a good time to start worrying.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "The lights are off again."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lights are off again.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "The lights are on."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lights are on.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "Finally the stabbing recedes. You c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Finally the stabbing recedes. You could try doing it again to see how painful it gets -- but you would probably die.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "Finally the pressure recedes. You f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Finally the pressure recedes. You find yourself covered in cold sweat and trying not to move -- hoping it will keep you from dying.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "You reach out to grab the tie... bu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You reach out to grab the tie... but what's this? Radiating chest pain! Fear washes over you.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "You can take it. Just breathe in sl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can take it. Just breathe in slowly.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "This is bad. Feels like sharp stone..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is bad. Feels like sharp stones grinding in your chest and keeping you from moving.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "For quite a long time."
fields.Dialogue Text: For quite a long time.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "You can take this one too. Just bre..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can take this one too. Just breathe in slowly.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "This fan has two chain pull switche..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This fan has two chain pull switches -- one ends in a tiny fan, the other in a light bulb. A truly horrific necktie has somehow attached itself to one of the blades.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Little black spots dance on your re..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Little black spots dance on your retinas. It's almost pleasurable.

fields.Title: You: "Grab your arm."
fields.Dialogue Text: Grab your arm.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "The blades come squeaking to a halt..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The blades come squeaking to a halt. It should be easier to reach the tie now.
fields.Alternate1: The blades come squeaking to a halt.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "An ominous, foreboding feeling fill..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An ominous, foreboding feeling fills you, as you look at the tie.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Oh no, it's happening again. You di..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh no, it's happening again. You didn't catch it and now there's numbness in half your chest.

fields.Title: You: "Press your hands to your chest to m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Press your hands to your chest to make sure your heart is still beating okay.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Oh no, it's happening again. You di..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh no, it's happening again. You didn't catch it and now there's numbness in your left arm, plus half your chest.

fields.Title: Endurance: "Do it -- *if you want to die*, the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Do it -- *if you want to die*, the stabbing pain in your chest is telling you. You're hanging by a thread here...

fields.Title: You: "Breathe in and out calmly."
fields.Dialogue Text: Breathe in and out calmly.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "You can take this. It's not nearly..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You can take this. It's not nearly as bad as the last time.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "You reach out to grab the tie... bu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You reach out to grab the tie... but what's this? Diffuse, radiating chest pain! Doom comes over you.

fields.Title: You: "Bring it on."
fields.Dialogue Text: Bring it on.

fields.Title: You: "Grab the tie."
fields.Dialogue Text: Grab the tie.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "The switch must be broken, because..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The switch must be broken, because nothing happens. The air in the room is starting to feel like vaporized urine.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Finally the pressure recedes. You f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Finally the pressure recedes. You find yourself covered in cold sweat. Try not to move too fast -- maybe that will keep you from collapsing.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "What you have in your hand is a fan..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What you have in your hand is a fantastically colourful tie, with four or five different patterns. The knot reminds you of a noose.

fields.Title: You: "Pull on the light bulb."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pull on the light bulb.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "The fan is spinning."
fields.Dialogue Text: The fan is spinning.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Still happening."
fields.Dialogue Text: Still happening.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Your eyes burn with photosensitivit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your eyes burn with photosensitivity. It's not good.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Or has it been consigned there as p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Or has it been consigned there as punishment? You feel as though this creature is your *friend* and wants to reattach itself to your neck. So that you may continue your adventures together in this strange world!

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "You swoop up and catch the tie... S..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You swoop up and catch the tie... Snap! It's released from the blade.
fields.Alternate1: You swoop up and catch the tie... snap! It's released from the blade. WARNING! WARNING! The necktie is no longer contained.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "It's just a little hangover-induced..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's just a little hangover-induced photosensitivity. Don't over-react.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Finally the stabbing recedes. You c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Finally the stabbing recedes. You could try doing it again to see how painful it gets. (Very.) But do you really want to risk it?

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "It's worse this time. Maybe you sho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's worse this time. Maybe you should stop trying to catch the tie?

fields.Title: You: "Breathe in calmly."
fields.Dialogue Text: Breathe in calmly.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "None of these is a real heart attac..."
fields.Dialogue Text: None of these is a real heart attack. This is such a joke. You should probably just exercise more.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Still bad. Definitely worse than th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Still bad. Definitely worse than the last time.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "This is not a *real* heart attack...."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is not a *real* heart attack. This is a joke. It's probably just your lungs or your oesophagus. The oesophagus does practically nothing.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "This is bad. Feels like sharp stone..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is bad. Feels like sharp stones grinding in your chest and keeping you from moving.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "It's even worse this time. Maybe yo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's even worse this time. Maybe you should stop trying to catch the tie?

fields.Title: Logic: "If it's your *friend*, why was it u..."
fields.Dialogue Text: If it's your *friend*, why was it up there? Who ties their friend to a ceiling fan? Maybe this thing is dangerous somehow...

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "A terrible mistake! Turn the lights..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A terrible mistake! Turn the lights off IMMEDIATELY! You can practically feel the photons burning a hole in your brain.

fields.Title: You: "Pull again to turn the lights off."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pull again to turn the lights off.

fields.Title: Interfacing: "You know what you should do? You sh..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You know what you should do? You should stop the fan and then try again, it'll get easier.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "For quite a long time."
fields.Dialogue Text: For quite a long time.

fields.Title: You: "Pull on the fan."
fields.Dialogue Text: Pull on the fan.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "This is not a *real* heart attack...."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is not a *real* heart attack. This is a joke. It's probably just your lungs or your oesophagus. The oesophagus does practically nothing.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "What you have in your hand is a tru..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What you have in your hand is a truly hideous necktie, with four or five different patterns. The knot reminds you of a noose.

fields.Title: Ceiling Fan: "Still happening. Definitely worse t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Still happening. Definitely worse than the last time.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "This isn't a real heart attack. You..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This isn't a real heart attack. You should probably just exercise more.
